rComments: Very difficult.  I wish I had taken this class at community college.  His exams are outrageous, you almost have to know the book the word for word.  He likes graphs, so study those.  I wish I had taken this class with someone else because of how hard it is.  I wish I had actually learned something.
Nice old man, I had fun listening to him
He gives really hard tests and barely prepares you for them at all. Most of his TAs are foreign and don't speak english very well.

Lectures were absolutely uselss in that he launched into some random story for half an hour. His notes were terrible and the grading on the tests were outrageous. Thank god I had a good TA. If you have the choice, take 103

Lectures and not very interesting. Most of it is just repeated from the text, so you don't have to attend. His pop quizzes are irritating as you have to attend the lectures since you don't know when he would give them. Haven't met him, so don't know how approachable he is during his office hours.
i liked him

Gottheil knows his economics, but to him lectures should be more about the fish markets. He has 4 pop-quizzes so just show up for the last 10 min of class. Book = lecture, because he wrote it. Hit or miss if you understand economics or not. Still the only MicroEcon teacher.
His teachings are irrelevant and the exams are very difficult.
Sucks

He is the worst professor I have ever had.  I managed to be one of the 10% of students that received an A, but I learned nothing from his lectures.  His lectures consist of a simple problem and a forty minute story  about something that happened either to him or someone in his family.  If you must have him, make sure to memorize the book!

Worst Class ever. The textbook he uses (which is written by him) is garbage. You need to read the book like your life depends on it. You may think that you understand the material but probably still fail the test. The aplia homework assignments are not even relevant to the test material. Total waste of time.
Great Professor!  He is completely approachable and easy to talk to.  If you're having trouble, go see him in his office hours - a fun interesting professor to learn from!

OMG!! This guy is probably one of the worst teachers I have ever had. He talks about so many pointless things during class. Be prepared for the best sleep of your life in Foellinger at 8 or 9am, trust me. Study the graphs in the book; he really seems to like them. The clicking he does with his tongue becomes less annoying as the semester goes on.
so hard,,,,,,,I wouldnt take this class if i were you...
Always friendly, perhaps a little boring.

READ THE BOOK, THEN READ IT AGAIN. THEN AFTER THAT DRAW OUT ALL THE GRAPHS AND MEMORIZE EACH ONE. THEN REDRAW THEM FROM MEMORY WITHOUT REFERENCING THE BOOK UNTIL THE END. MAKE SURE TO MEMORIZE ALL DEFINITIONS BECAUSE THOSE RANDOMLY SHOW UP ON YOUR TWO TESTS THAT COUNT FOR 72% OF YOUR GRADE!!! WORST CLASS EVER!!!!!!!
ECON 102 with Gottheil may be the closest thing to a living hell i have ever experienced.
If u study the graphs and formulas u should be fine.  do not pay attention to statistics and history.
Do not pay attention to statistics and definitions.  Just memorize the graphs and formulas and you should be fine.

OMG...OMG...HOnestly I took his class just for major core requirement. He's totally notorious in our campus. As he will tell you, if you just regard your textbooks as your bible, He will bless you. -v- Even thoug his class is not that clear but, as a fresh, pure memorizing is quite easy, and it will help you make a good base for future econ courses
